definition: to cut off (a length)/to stop/to intercept/section/chunk/length

sentences.english: As of Tuesday, the volcano in Iceland was still erupting, though the cloud was lower.
sentences.chinese: 截至週二，冰島火山仍在噴發，但火山灰雲有所降低。

sentences.english: As of today, nearly 30,000 confirmed cases have been reported in 74 countries.

sentences.english: As of noon on Saturday, the water had risen to within 20 meters of the mine opening.
sentences.chinese: 截至星期六中午，水位已上升到距礦井口約20米處。

sentences.english: More than 24 inches (61 centimeters) of snow had fallen in parts of New England by the evening of January 12.

sentences.english: At the end of last month, it had 7 projects for pre-sales.

sentences.english: Emissions to 2008 have already released half of this.

sentences.english: Up to the 20th of May about 500 people have visited the art exhibition.

sentences.english: The unrests have killed 74 people and injured 530.

sentences.english: By now the number of the attacks in the city was making it almost impossible for the police to keep up.
sentences.chinese: 截至目前，襲擊次數之多幾乎使警方無力招架。

sentences.english: Up to now, Tianjin Binhai New Area of the Green Wave Control of roads have been increased to 6.

sentences.english: As of late 2004, however, it remains semi-autonomous.
sentences.chinese: 截至2004年底，但是，它仍然是半自治。

sentences.english: Forman and his team did not respond to requests for comment by deadline.
sentences.chinese: 福曼和他的團隊截至目前沒有發表任何評論。
